    "long_instructions": "1. **Create a New Feature**\r\n\r\nDraw a card from the deck and prompt AI to create that feature. Re-prompt AI as needed.\r\n\r\n2. **Save with a Comment**\r\n\r\nWhen the feature looks good, navigate to the Version History tab. Describe your changes and click \"Save version\".\r\n\r\n3. **Revert as Needed**  \r\n\r\nAfter 5 minutes, or when prompted by your teacher, revert to the most recent version you saved with a description.\r\n\r\n:::details [**Why go back to an old version?**]\r\nSometimes new code breaks things that used to work. In that case, developers “revert” — they go back to a previous version that worked correctly. It’s important to save your changes with short, clear messages, so you can easily find and restore the right version later.\r\n:::",
